  "original_title": "IMF would need commitment from administration \u2013 CBSL Chief",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "IMF would need commitment from administration \u2013 CBSL Chief",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); Governor of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka (CBSL) Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe says he is confident that Sri Lanka can come out of the prevalent crisis within a period of 04 \u2013 05 months.",
        "\u201cWe have a clear program and a clear path,\u201d he said, adding \u201cif we follow this path\u2026 I am confident that we can come out of this crisis\u2026 say for example in about 04 \u2013 05 months\u2026 Until then we will have a difficult time.\u201d Dr. Weerasinghe added he is hopeful that people would be patient until Sri Lanka can ride out the crisis situation over the next couple of months.",
        "In an interview with CNN, Dr. Weerasinghe was of the view that the country will certainly benefit from the economic reforms being implemented and the reforms that are to be implemented in the future.",
        "He also said that if there was continued stable administration Sri Lanka could have reached the IMF staff-level agreement within this month (July).",
        "\u201cBut if there is a delay in forming an administration, then, of course, IMF needs a commitment from the new administration of the policies that we have presented to the IMF at the technical level. So the time of that process will depend on the new administration approach,\u201d he said.",
        "Sri Lanka: Police hunt for three heroin peddlers after Rs. 380 Mn heroin bust in Embilipitiya"
      ],
